08 and played for one season. On 15 July 2013 he signed an annual contract with [[Iraklis Thessaloniki F.C.|Iraklis]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Iraklis F.C. |url=http://www.fciraklis.gr/nea/press/item/572-%CF%80%CE%BF%CE%B4%CE%BF%CF%83%CF%86%CE%B1%CE%B9%CF%81%CE%B9%CF%83%CF%84%CE%AE%CF%82-%CF%84%CE%BF%CF%85-%CE%B7%CF%81%CE%B1%CE%BA%CE%BB%CE%B7-%CE%BF-%CF%84%CE%AC%CF%83%CE%BF%CF%82-%CE%BA%CF%85%CF%81%CE%B9%CE%AC%CE%BA%CE%BF%CF%82 |script-title=el:\u03a0\u03bf\u03b4\u03bf\u03c3\u03c6\u03b1\u03b9\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03ae\u03c2 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u0397\u03a1\u0391\u039a\u039b\u0397 \u03bf \u03a4\u03ac\u03c3\u03bf\u03c2 \u039a\u03c5\u03c1\u03b9\u03ac\u03ba\u03bf\u03c2 |date=15 July 2013 |accessdate=28 August 2013 |language=el |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130718141432/http://www.fciraklis.gr/nea/press/item/572-%CF%80%CE%BF%CE%B4%CE%BF%CF%83%CF%86%CE%B1%CE%B9%CF%81%CE%B9%CF%83%CF%84%CE%AE%CF%82-%CF%84%CE%BF%CF%85-%CE%B7%CF%81%CE%B1%CE%BA%CE%BB%CE%B7-%CE%BF-%CF%84%CE%AC%CF%83%CE%BF%CF%82-%CE%BA%CF%85%CF%81%CE%B9%CE%AC%CE%BA%CE%BF%CF%82 |archivedate=18 July 2013 |df=dmy }}</ref> In January 2014, Kyriakos signed a contract with [[Football League (Greece)|Greek Football League]] club [[Paniliakos F.C.]].\n\nThe transfer from Kallithea F.C. to Olympiacos F.C. was by some seen as a surprise move despite the fact that Olympiacos F.C. had competition for the signature of the player. Rumors in the Greek media, Ethnospor among others, claimed that Br\u00f8ndby IF and their head coach Michael Laudrup expressed their interest in Kyriakos just before Olympiacos F.C. signed him.\n\n==Honours==\n'''[[AC Omonia|Omonia]]'''\n*[[Cypriot First Division|Cypriot Championship]]: [[Cypriot First Division 2009-10|2009\u201310]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.scoresway.com/?sport=soccer&page=player&id=18854 Scoresway Profile]\n*[http://www.onsports.gr/onstats/?url=/soccer/player/main.php&sport-select=soccer&player-select=531 P